# Optional. Copy to .env only if you want to override defaults. Never commit .env.
#
# Without any env vars, the app:
#   - Auto-generates and stores a secret key in .secret_key (created on first run)
#   - Uses DEBUG=0 (production mode)
#   - Allows home.freedomwoods.online, localhost, 127.0.0.1
#   - Uses SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT=0 (for Cloudflare Tunnel / reverse proxy)
#
# Override only when needed:
# DJANGO_DEBUG=1
# DJANGO_ALLOWED_HOSTS=other.example.com
# DJANGO_CSRF_TRUSTED_ORIGINS=https://other.example.com
# DJANGO_SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT=1
#
# Contact form → Gmail. Copy to .env in the PROJECT ROOT (same folder as manage.py).
# Use a Gmail App Password: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# No spaces around =. No quotes unless the value has spaces.
# EMAIL_HOST_USER=your@gmail.com
# EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your-16-char-app-password
# CONTACT_EMAIL=your@gmail.com
